  "texts": [
    "Account and source scores are calculated iteratively according to the strength of interactions between nodes from the two network partitions, until convergence:u t+1 i = αu 0 i + (1 -α) j G ij d t j ℓ G iℓ, (10)d t+1 j = βd 0 + (1 -β) i G ij u t i ℓ G ℓj,(11)respectively, where α and β are the teleportation factors for accounts and sources respectively, d 0 = 1/|D| is the initial value for sources, and u 0 i is the initial value for account i, defined as:u 0 i = ⎧ ⎪ ⎪ ⎨ ⎪ ⎪ ⎩ 0 ifi ∈ H, 1 ifi ∈ L, 1/|U| otherwise.",
    "(12)These initial values are further normalized such that i∈U u 0 i = 1.",
    "The scores are normalized, so no further normalization is necessary.",
    "BGRMBGRM [38] is similar to Co-HITS.",
    "The main difference is in the way they normalize node scores at each iteration (see Table 1 in [39] for more details)."
  ],
